  "session_header": "[SESSION_HEADER]\nTimestamp: 1492 DR, Mirtul 15, 18:48:28\nLocation: A Small Stone Chamber\nStatus: Lvl 1 Fighter | HP: 12/12 | XP: 0/300 | Gold: 10gp",
  "resources": "HD: 1/1 | Exhaustion: 0",
  "narrative": "Morning light filters through a narrow arrow slit in the rough-hewn stone walls, illuminating a small chamber barely large enough for two to stand comfortably. The air smells of damp earth and old mortar. A single wooden door, reinforced with iron bands, stands opposite you—the only exit from this space that has served as your temporary shelter.\n\nYour head throbs with the dull ache of a restless night, and your stomach growls reminding you that it's been since yesterday since you've eaten. The door appears firmly shut, and you can hear faint sounds from beyond—muffled voices and the clatter of metal.\n\nA small pile of your belongings sits in the corner: your travel-worn backpack, a shortsword, and the chain shirt you earned from your late master.",
  "planning_block": {
    "thinking": "I'm trapped in a small stone chamber. The door is shut and there are voices beyond. I need to figure out my situation and find a way out. I have my shortsword and chain shirt, but I'm not equipped for a direct fight if there are multiple enemies. My best attributes are Strength (16) and Constitution (14), making me physically capable but not particularly skilled in stealth or social situations.",
